  "prompt": "Upto which rank does a reserved category student get IRS (IT)?",
  "response": "The allocation of services in the Indian Revenue Service (IRS) under the Income Tax (IT) department for Reserved Category students (such as SC, ST, OBC, and EWS) depends on their rank in the **Civil Services Examination (CSE)** conducted by the Union Public Service Commission (UPSC). \n\nThe cutoff rank for IRS (IT) varies each year based on factors like the number of vacancies, the difficulty of the exam, and the performance of candidates. However, general trends can be observed based on previous years:\n\n1. **For SC/ST Candidates**: \n   - IRS (IT) allocation can go up to **rank 800\u20131000** in some years, depending on the vacancies and cutoff.\n\n2. **For OBC Candidates**: \n   - The cutoff generally lies between **rank 400\u2013600** for IRS (IT).\n\n3. **For EWS Candidates**: \n   - The cutoff is usually around **rank 300\u2013500** for IRS (IT).\n\nThese ranks are approximate and can vary each year. For the most accurate and updated information, refer to the **UPSC CSE Final Result** and **Service Allocation** notifications for the specific CSE year. \n\n### Note:\nCandidates with higher ranks may also opt for IRS (IT) if they choose it as their preference, even if they are in a position to get higher services like IAS or IPS. The final allocation depends on the candidate\u2019s preferences, rank, and category.",
